column1:
Categories: Coffee & Tea, Food, Coffee Roasteries | Review: Great hip coffee with two locations in Santa Barbara. They use Verve coffee beans from Santa Cruz. 

// PARKING // Street or public lots. 

// FOOD // 
     + Shakerato: Had to try their famous drink. 2 shots of espresso shaken in a shaker with ice and simple syrup. It is served in a small cappuccino cup over some ice. It is very bold without being too strong. If you are someone who likes to sip on a drink for a long time though, this is not for you because it is about half a capuccino cup max in terms of quantity. 
    + Iced coffee with soy milk: Creamy with bold coffee flavor. Reminiscent of Joe's Coffee in NYC

*Their other location has a small parking lot.
